# Python standards

- Python 3.12, type hints on every function and model field.
- Pydantic v2 for all data contracts (mirror `references/design/02-data-contracts.md`).
- Config via `pydantic-settings` in `src/common/config.py`; never read `os.environ` ad hoc outside it.
- Async for I/O (HTTP to Stepfun/Ollama/ComfyUI). No blocking calls in async paths.
- Structure: `src/common` (config, schemas, clients), `src/agents` (one file per agent), `src/optimizer`, `src/orchestrator`.
- Error handling: raise typed exceptions; never swallow. Agent failures return structured errors, not silent `None`.
- Logging via `structlog` or stdlib `logging`; structured records with `run_id`, `agent`, `latency_s`. Never log secrets.
- Validate JSON files on write AND read against the Pydantic schema.

## Lint/format

- `ruff check .` and `ruff format .` must pass.
- `mypy src` must pass with no new errors.
- No debug `print()` in committed code — use the logger.

## Example — typed agent call

```python
async def analyze_brand(brief: str, image: Path, name: str) -> BrandDna:
    resp = await stepfun.chat(
        model=settings.stepfun_vlm_model,
        messages=[{"role": "user", "content": [
            {"type": "text", "text": analyst_prompt(brief, name)},
            {"type": "image_url", "image_url": {"url": image_to_data_url(image)}},
        ]}],
        reasoning_effort="high",
    )
    dna = BrandDna.model_validate_json(resp)
    return dna
```
